77a\">Chat with our team</h3><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Share your situation and we&#x27;ll recommend the best park, indoor option, or community meetup.</p><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a support-actions\"><a href=\"/contact\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Contact us</a><a href=\"/signup\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a secondary\">Join community</a></div></div></aside><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-main\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-rail\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-eyebrow\">Popular right now</span><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Tap to jump to the full answer.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip-row\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>How much does a dog license cost in Arlington, VA?</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>Are there indoor dog parks in Arlington?</button></div></div><div role=\"list\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-accordion\"><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">01</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">How much does a dog license cost in Arlington, VA?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Arlington County offers a unique lifetime dog license for a one-time fee of $30.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">legal</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Arlington County offers a unique lifetime dog license for a one-time fee of $30. This license remains valid for the life of the dog as long as the rabies vaccination is kept current, making it very pet-owner friendly compared to annual renewals.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->legal</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">02</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Are there indoor dog parks in Arlington?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Yes—Arlington is home to Snouts &amp; Stouts, a massive 12,000+ sq ft indoor dog park and bar.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Facilities &amp; Features</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Yes—Arlington is home to Snouts &amp; Stouts, a massive 12,000+ sq ft indoor dog park and bar. It provides K9 grass, climate control, and supervised play so your dog can socialize while you enjoy a local brew.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Facilities &amp; Features</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">03</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Which Arlington dog parks have water access?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Shirlington Dog Park and Glencarlyn Park both offer unique stream access.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Facilities &amp; Features</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Shirlington Dog Park and Glencarlyn Park both offer unique stream access. Shirlington features a fenced-in entry to Four Mile Run, allowing dogs to swim and splash safely in a natural environment.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Facilities &amp; Features</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">04</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Can I take my dog to watch planes at Gravelly Point?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Absolutely.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Planning Your Visit</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Absolutely. Leashed dogs are welcome at Gravelly Point Park along the Mount Vernon Trail. It’s a famous spot for watching planes land at Reagan National Airport, though it can be very loud for noise-sensitive pets.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Planning Your Visit</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article></div></div></div></div></section></div></section><section id=\"related-resources\" class=\"related-resources-section\"><div class=\"section-shell\"><div class=\"section-heading\"><span class=\"section-eyebrow\">Keep exploring</span><h2>More ways to plan</h2><p>Browse statewide guides, submit a listing, or connect with our team.</p></div><div class=\"resources-grid\"><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-globe\"></i></div><h3>California overview</h3><p>See every city we cover plus statewide insights.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/contact\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-chat-dots\"></i></div><h3>Ask the team</h3><p>Need custom data or media assets? We’re here.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/list-your-park\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-megaphone\"></i></div><h3>Feature your park</h3><p>Upgrade to a featured listing and reach active pet parents.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a><a class=\"resource-card\" href=\"/blog\"><div class=\"resource-icon\"><i class=\"bi bi-journal-text\"></i></div><h3>Latest guides</h3><p>Training tips, travel itineraries, and product spotlights.</p><i class=\"bi bi-arrow-up-right\"></i></a></div></div></section></main><footer class=\"footer-new\"><div class=\"footer-container\"><div class=\"footer-grid\"><div class=\"footer-column\"><h4 class=\"footer-heading\">IndoorDogPark</h4><ul class=\"footer-links\"><li><a href=\"/about\">About us</a></li><li><a href=\"/partners\">Partners</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"footer-column\"><h4 class=\"footer-heading\">Discover</h4><ul class=\"footer-links\"><li><a href=\"/\">Browse parks</a></li><li><a href=\"/how-it-works\">How it works</a></li><li><a href=\"/blog\">Blog</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"footer-column\"><h4 class=\"footer-heading\">Park Owners</h4><ul class=\"footer-links\"><li><a href=\"/list-your-park\">List your park</a></li><li><a href=\"/owner-resources\">Owner resources</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"footer-column\"><h4 class=\"footer-heading\">Support</h4><ul class=\"footer-links\"><li><a href=\"/contact\">Contact us</a></li><li><a href=\"/faq\">FAQ</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"footer-column col-span-full md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-1\"><h4 class=\"footer-heading\">Join the Pack</h4><p class=\"mb-4 text-sm text-white/70\">Get the latest indoor dog park news and updates.</p><div class=\"rounded-2xl border b