\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":9,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/glencarlyn-park\",\"name\":\"Glencarlyn Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/glencarlyn-park\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about Glencarlyn Park.  What makes this dog facility special is its spacious, professional, reliable. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience for both...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Arlington\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":10,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/the-royal-pet-resort-and-spa\",\"name\":\"The Royal Pet Resort and Spa\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/the-royal-pet-resort-and-spa\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about The Royal Pet Resort and Spa.  What makes this dog facility special is its professional, reliable, clean. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Arlington\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}25:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2d\"}}]\n2e:T590,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How much does a dog license cost in Arlington, VA?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Arlington County offers a unique lifetime dog license for a one-time fee of $30. This license remains valid for the life of the dog as long as the rabies vaccination is kept current, making it very pet-owner friendly compared to annual renewals.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there indoor dog parks in Arlington?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes—Arlington is home to Snouts & Stouts, a massive 12,000+ sq ft indoor dog park and bar. It provides K9 grass, climate control, and supervised play so your dog can socialize while you enjoy a local brew.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Which Arlington dog parks have water access?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Shirlington Dog Park and Glencarlyn Park both offer unique stream access. Shirlington features a fenced-in entry to Four Mile Run, allowing dogs to swim and splash safely in a natural environment.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I take my dog to watch planes at Gravelly Point?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Absolutely. Leashed dogs are welcome at Gravelly Point Park along the Mount Vernon Trail. It’s a famous spot for watching planes land at Reagan National Airport, though it can be very loud for noise-sensitive pets.\"}}]}26:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2e\"}}]\n27:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Arlington\\\"}]}\"}}]\n28:[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n29:[\"$\",\"$L2f\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n2a:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Arlington\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"City spotlight\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks in Arlington, VA\"}],\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Experience the premier pet culture of Arlington, from the historic stream-access runs of Shirlington to the year-round indoor play at Snouts & Stouts.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Arlington, Virginia, stands as a premier destination for urban dog owners, offering a sophisticated infrastructure that balances high-density living with expansive, world-class pet amenities. The county is anchored by the historic \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://parks.arlingtonva.us/locations/shirlington-dog-park/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Shirlington Dog Park\"}],null,\", which was the first off-leash facility in the D.C. area and remains a crown jewel for its unique fenced-in access to Four Mile Run, allowing pups a safe natural swim. For those seeking climate-controlled socialization, \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.snoutsandstouts.com/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Snouts & Stouts\"}],null,\" provides a massive 12,000-square-foot indoor park and bar, featuring professional K9 grass and a \\\"beer and treats\\\" concept that caters to the local community year-round. This commitment to canine inclusion is further reflected in the county’s pet-friendly administrative policies, such as the unique $30 lifetime dog license, which eliminates the hassle of annual renewals for residents who keep their rabies vaccinations current.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Beyond the urban runs, Arlington offers iconic outdoor experiences along the \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.nps.gov/gwmp/planyourvisit/mtvernon-trail.htm\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Mount Vernon Trail\"}],null,\", where leashed dogs can accompany their owners to highlights like Gravelly Point Park to experience the roar of planes descending into Reagan National Airport. Local favorite \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://lostdogcafe.com/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Lost Dog Cafe\"}],null,\" in Westover further enriches the culture, as its success supports a rescue foundation that has saved tens of thousands of animals, making dining out a philanthropic tradition for local dog lovers. For those exploring the market for new pet facilities, our \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"7\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/owner-resources\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"owner resources\"}],null,\" detail the high demand and zoning nuances found in vibrant districts like Clarendon and Rosslyn. Whether splashing in the stream at \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"10\",{\"href\":\"https://parks.arlingtonva.us/locations/glencarlyn-park-dog-park/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Glencarlyn Park\"}],null,\" or relaxing on a brewery patio, Arlington provides a world-class environment where pets are truly integrated into every facet of civic life.\"]}]]}],\"$L31\",\"$L32\"]}],\"$L33\"]}]}],\"$L34\",\"$L35\",\"$L36\",\"$L37\",\"$L38\",\"$L39\",\"$L3a\",\"$L3b\",\"$L3c\",\"$L3d\",\"$L3e\",\"$L3f\"]}]\n2b:[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-new\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-container\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-grid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-column\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h4\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-heading\",\"children\":\"IndoorDogPark\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-links\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/about\",\"children\":\"About us\"}]}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/